🚀 Task 3: Create Custom Policy (Very Important 💥)
🎯 Scenario

Developer should:

Start/Stop EC2
NOT delete instances
🛠️ Policy JSON
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "ec2:StartInstances",
        "ec2:StopInstances",
        "ec2:DescribeInstances"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}
Steps
IAM → Policies → Create Policy
Paste JSON
Attach to Developer group
📚 Learn
Fine-grained permissions
Real enterprise control
🚀 Task 4: IAM Role for EC2 (MOST IMPORTANT ⭐)
🎯 Scenario

EC2 needs access to S3 (without storing credentials)

🛠️ Steps
IAM → Roles → Create Role
Select:
AWS Service → EC2
Attach policy:
AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess
Attach role to EC2 instance
📚 Learn
Secure service-to-service access
No hardcoded credentials
